│ incoming block index.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s): We need to add a check  │
│ to ensure we only treat the gather as PHI incoming values when `Entry` is   │
│ actually a PHI instruction node (not a SplitVectorize node) and `Op` is     │
│ correctly linked to it. The fix is to verify that `Op->UserTreeIndex.UserTE │
│ == Entry` and that `Entry` is not in a special state like                   │
│ SplitVectorize.\n\n5. Conclusion: The fix adds proper validation before     │
│ accessing PHI incoming blocks, preventing the out-of-bounds access that     │
│ causes the crash."                                                          │
